NBA’s Oldest Active Player Kurt Thomas Signs With Portland Trail Blazers

-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 
2011-12-12T14:42:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-12/nba-s-oldest-active-player-kurt-thomas-signs-with-portland-trail-blazers.html
Kurt Thomas, the oldest active
player in the  National Basketball Association , signed with the
Portland Trail Blazers.  The signing of the 39-year-old forward was announced on the
team’s  website . Terms weren’t disclosed. Thomas is one day older
than Phoenix Suns forward Grant Hill.  Thomas played in 52 games last year for the  Chicago Bulls ,
averaging 4.1 points and 5.8 rebounds per game.  Thomas was selected by the Miami Heat with the 10th pick in
the 1995 NBA Draft. In 16 seasons with eight teams, including
the New York Knicks and Dallas Mavericks, Thomas has scored
8,716 points and grabbed 7,051 rebounds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eben Novy-Williams in New York at 
 enovywilliam@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net  